ience by providing readers with choices and consequences that impact the narrative.\n\n**Methodology:**\nThis study employed a mixed-methods approach, combining qualitative and quantitative data collection and analysis methods. A survey of 100 ORV novel readers was conducted to gather information on their reading habits, preferences, and experiences with the genre. Additionally, a content analysis of 20 ORV novels was performed to identify common narrative structures, character development strategies, and interactive elements.\n\n**Results:**\nThe survey results revealed that ORV novel readers value the interactive elements and immersive world-building that these novels provide. The majority of respondents (80%) reported that they enjoy making choices that impact the story, and 70% stated that they appreciate the complexity and depth of the world-building in ORV novels. The content analysis revealed that ORV novels often employ non-linear narrative structures, featuring multiple branching storylines and character arcs. The use of character customization, skill trees, and quest systems was also prevalent, with 90% of the analyzed novels incorporating at least one of these elements.\n\n**Discussion:**\nThe findings of this study suggest that ORV novels offer a unique reading experience that combines the best elements of video games, role-playing games, and traditional literature. The interactive elements and immersive world-building in ORV novels engage readers and provide a sense of agency and control over the narrative. The use of character customization, skill trees, and quest systems adds a layer of complexity and depth to the story, allowing readers to invest in the characters and their development.\n\n**Conclusion:**\nThis research contributes to our understanding of the ORV novel genre and its appeal to readers. The study's findings highlight the importance of interactive elements, immersive world-building, and character development in creating an engaging read